						               													<description>WE SAW SPAIN DIE is a solitary game simulating military operations during the Spanish Civil War (July 18 1936 - April 1 1939)&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The board covers the historical space of this conflict. &amp;#10;The goal of the game is to reduce the Republican morale and increase the Nationalists morale.&amp;#10;To get those victory/morale points, areas must be captured, provinces and main towns that are military objectives.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;As a player you are in charge of the Nationalist group and try to topple the Republican government elected in 1936.&amp;#10;In a context of European division between democracies and dictatorships, you get support from Nazi Germany , Fascist Italy and the authoritarian Portuguese regime. &amp;#10;The player gets to pick different combat strategies to achieve his goal - Mass attack, Safe progress, Armoured attack, coordinated maneuvers or a non-combat reinforcements action.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;1 turn = 3 months&amp;#10;12 turns total&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Game published in French&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
